4 Olympic Games will dazzle with an unforgettable, star-studded opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"C\\u00e9line Dion and Lady Gaga will grace the stage in a highly anticipated duet, marking a spectacular comeback for Dion and a thrilling addition to Gaga's repertoire.\", \"from\": 495, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.820871282685827e-40, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French President Emmanuel Macron inadvertently spilled the beans about the surprise act.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 677, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Macron shared his excitement: \\\"Apparently she has arrived in Paris, it's great!\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 750, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.559417629229896e-16, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 811, \"end\": 816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.616827400988261e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I would be immensely happy if she could be at this opening ceremony, like all our compatriots.\\\"\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He continued with a playful smile, \\\"I will not reveal anything, what [opening ceremony director] Thomas Jolly and all his teams have prepared.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is also a surprise.\\\"\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rumour mill suggests that the iconic duo will perform \\u00c9dith Piaf's timeless classic,La Vie en Rose, according toThe Guardian  This performance will pay a poignant homage to French culture, delivered by two of the music industry's biggest names.\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"score\": 0.9999999997958184, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"\\u00c9dith Piaf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\"}, {\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"C\\u00e9line Dion's appearance is particularly significant.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1349, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"C\\u00e9line Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been largely out of the public eye since her diagnosis of Stiff Person Syndrome in December 2022.\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This rareneurological disorderhas forced her to pause her career and retreat from the limelight.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her last live performance was in New York in spring 2020.\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1642, \"end\": 1650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999999995151029, \"rank\": 4.848878730959587e-09, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite her health struggles, Dion's determination to return to the stage is evident.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As she prepared for this major comeback, she arrived in Paris on a private jet.\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.616827400988261e-22, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She stayed in a luxurious suite at the Royal Monceau on the Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es.\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1896, \"end\": 1910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9938637728104254, \"rank\": 0.005341849563968814, \"text\": \"Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lady Gaga, too, has been in the spotlight recently, according to theIndependent.\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The American singer, known for her dynamic performances, was spotted aboard a floating piano on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1999, \"end\": 2007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998530834199, \"rank\": 9.562209321964308e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2095, \"end\": 2106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her French connections run deep; her mother is half French.\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.993955152312059, \"rank\": 0.006074629846143521, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbp